A 4-inch by 6-inch picture is enlarged for framing by tripling its dimensions. A 2-inch-wide border is then placed around each side of the enlarged picture, as shown in the diagram below. Thin metal framing is sold only in increments of one foot. What is the minimum number of linear feet of framing that must be purchased to go around the perimeter of the border? egin{tikzpicture}\draw[thick] (0,0) rectangle (7,4);\draw (1,1) rectangle (6,3);
ode at (3.5,3.2) {border};
ode at (3.5,2) {picture};
ode[right] at (7,1) {frame};\draw[->] (7.5,1) -- (6.5,1);\draw[->] (5.5,1) -- (6,1);\end{tikzpicture}

